## §3 — CONCURRENCY & LIFECYCLE (P2)

### Go scans

```bash
# 1. Every goroutine — does it respect ctx.Done()?
rg -n "go\s+func\(" pkgs/ internal/ cmd/ --type go -A 5

# 2. Mutex locks — every Lock matched with deferred Unlock?
rg -n "\.Lock\(\)" pkgs/ internal/ --type go -A 3 | rg -v "defer.*Unlock"

# 3. Background context in request paths (should be r.Context())
rg -n "context\.Background\(\)|context\.TODO\(\)" pkgs/tasks/handler/ pkgs/tasks/store/ --type go

# 4. SSE hub subscribers — registration/cleanup symmetry
#    Find where subscribers are added vs where they're removed
rg -n "subscribe|Subscribe" pkgs/tasks/handler/ --type go -A 2
rg -n "unsubscribe|Unsubscribe|delete\(.*subscribers" pkgs/tasks/handler/ --type go

# 5. time.After in select loops (leak)
rg -n "time\.After\(" pkgs/ internal/ cmd/ --type go -B 1 -A 3 | rg -B 2 "select"

# 6. HTTP clients without timeout
rg -n "&http\.Client\{" pkgs/ internal/ cmd/ --type go -A 5 | rg -v "Timeout:"

# 7. Channel sends without context-aware select (block on full buffer)
rg -n "<-\s*[a-zA-Z]" pkgs/tasks/handler/ --type go | rg -v "select|case"
```

### Web scans

```bash
# 1. useEffect with fetch but no AbortController
rg -n "useEffect" web/src/ --type tsx -A 15 | rg -B 8 "fetch\(|axios\." | rg -v "AbortController|signal"

# 2. EventSource without close in cleanup
rg -n "new EventSource\(" web/src/ --type ts --type tsx -A 20 | rg -B 1 "\.close\(\)"

# 3. setInterval/setTimeout without clear in cleanup
rg -n "setInterval\(|setTimeout\(" web/src/ --type ts --type tsx -A 5 | rg -B 1 "clearInterval|clearTimeout"

# 4. Effects whose cleanup depends on stale closures (manual review)
rg -n "useEffect" web/src/ --type tsx -A 30 | rg -B 25 "return\s*\(\s*\)\s*=>"
```

**What to look for:**
- A goroutine whose loop has `for { ... }` without `case <-ctx.Done():` → P2 leak
- A `Lock()` without an immediate-following `defer Unlock()` → potential deadlock
- A subscriber added with no clear matching removal path → SSE hub leak
- `time.After` inside a `select` that loops — switch to `time.NewTimer` with `Stop`
- React `useEffect` doing fetch with no abort signal → stale-response bug

