## §5 — INTEGRATION / CONTRACT DRIFT (P5)

### Cross-doc checks

```bash
# 1. Every T2A_* env var in code vs every T2A_* env var in docs/RUNTIME-ENV.md
rg -no "T2A_[A-Z_]+" pkgs/ internal/ cmd/ --type go | sort -u > /tmp/code-envs.txt
rg -no "T2A_[A-Z_]+" docs/RUNTIME-ENV.md | sort -u > /tmp/doc-envs.txt
diff /tmp/code-envs.txt /tmp/doc-envs.txt
# Lines only in code → undocumented env. Lines only in docs → stale doc.

# 2. Every handler route in code vs every route in docs/API-HTTP.md
rg -no '("(GET|POST|PATCH|DELETE|PUT)\s+/[a-zA-Z0-9/{}_]+")' pkgs/tasks/handler/ --type go | sort -u
rg -no '`(GET|POST|PATCH|DELETE|PUT)\s+/[a-zA-Z0-9/{}_]+`' docs/API-HTTP.md | sort -u

# 3. SSE event names: Go emit sites vs Web subscribe sites
rg -n 'event:\s*["`][a-z_]+["`]|EventName.*=.*"[a-z_]+"' pkgs/tasks/handler/ --type go
rg -n 'addEventListener\(["`][a-z_]+["`]|case\s+["`][a-z_]+["`]' web/src/ --type ts --type tsx
```

### parseTaskApi audit

```bash
# 1. Find every fetch site in web/src/api/
rg -n "fetch\(" web/src/api/ --type ts

# 2. For each, confirm the response goes through parseTaskApi (or sibling)
rg -n "parseTaskApi|parseTask\b|parseCycle" web/src/api/ --type ts

# 3. Confirm web/src/ outside web/src/api/ never calls fetch directly
rg -n "fetch\(" web/src/ --type ts --type tsx -g '!**/api/**'
# Any hits here = P5 violation (bypasses the parser chokepoint)
```

### Status code honesty

```bash
# Find every WriteHeader / WriteJSONError call in handlers; cross-check against docs
rg -n "WriteHeader\(http\.Status|WriteJSONError" pkgs/tasks/handler/ --type go
```

For each, manually verify: does `docs/API-HTTP.md` say this route returns this code on this condition? If not, the doc OR the code is wrong — that's the defect.

### Time / timezone audit

```bash
# Server-side: time.Now() (UTC by default in Go) — usage in stored values
rg -n "time\.Now\(\)" pkgs/tasks/store/ --type go

# Web-side: Date parsing
rg -n "new Date\(" web/src/ --type ts --type tsx
# Suspicious: `new Date(serverString)` where serverString is RFC3339 with Z → JS treats as UTC, displays in local. Verify intent.
```

